article.headline: Niagara 79, Marist 50
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP)Rob Garrison scored 21 points to lead four scorers in double figures as second-seeded Niagara cruised to a 79-50 win against 10th-seeded Marist in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference tournament's quarterfinal round Saturday. Tyrone Lewis added 13 points and Demetrius Williamson had 12 for the Purple Eagles (25-7, 15-4 MAAC). The game was never in doubt for Niagara, which led wire-to-wire and went into the second half on a 10-0 run that bridged the halftime break. Benson Egemonye added 11 points and nine rebounds. Ryan Schneider scored 12 points -- including his 1,000th career point, which came on a late 3-pointer -- and grabbed 12 rebounds for the Red Foxes (10-23, 5-15 MAAC). They also got 12 points from Kaylen Gregory and 10 from David Devezin. Marist shot just 33 percent from the floor and 36 percent (9-for-25) from the free-throw line. Niagara took a 39-23 lead into the break.
